The refinery currently merges any PR that passes quality gates, regardless of author. On shared/enterprise monorepos this is wrong — committing other people's work violates team conventions and can bypass review processes that are external to the codebase.

Add a configurable author filter to MergeQueueConfig so the refinery only considers PRs authored by (or attributed to) specified user IDs.

Suggested config shape:
```json
{
  "merge_queue": {
    "author_filter": ["mccraigmccraig"],
    // or: "author_filter": "self" (derive from gh auth status)
  }
}
```

Context: The sona rig's refinery merged 4 PRs authored by other team members on an enterprise monorepo (sona-is/sona), using the operator's gh credentials. The merges showed as the operator's user, which is misleading and bypasses team-specific merge governance.
